cs.LG, cs.CR, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.DS 

This paper focuses on the black-box attack setting in deep neural networks, which is a common topic in machine learning and computer security. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also discusses adversarial attacks, which is a common topic in computer security, suggesting cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) as the second likely category. The paper also uses image datasets and discusses active learning, suggesting cs.CV (Computer Vision) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as likely categories. Finally, the paper uses state-of-the-art white-box attack methods, suggesting cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) as a possible category.
